<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>JeffCaulfield</title><subtitle>© 2017 Jeff Caulfield | CC BY 4.0 |  </subtitle><link href="http://jeffcaulfield.com/atom.xml" rel="self"></link><link href="http://jeffcaulfield.com"></link><id>d8a4c0c8-df4a-5965-13e7-d0e30979de08</id><updated>2017-10-22T20:42:25</updated><entry><title>2017-10-22 In Vera Veritas</title><link href="http://jeffcaulfield.com/#2017-10-22%20In%20Vera%20Veritas"></link><link href="http://jeffcaulfield.com/static/2017-10-22%2520In%2520Vera%2520Veritas.html" rel="alternative" type="text/html"></link><id>97822d23-ad1d-ee24-8fe0-a98aeb481bb7</id><updated>2017-10-22T13:26:45</updated><content type="xhtml"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p>My next idea is to provide a cryptographic signature file to verify that the stand-alone HTML file was actually authored by me.</p><p>The first step is use <a class="tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves" href="#GnuPrivacyGuard">GnuPrivacyGuard</a> to <a class="tc-tiddlylink-external" href="https://alexcabal.com/creating-the-perfect-gpg-keypair/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">generate</a> a cryptographic key pair and <a class="tc-tiddlylink-external" href="http://www.gushi.org/make-dns-cert/HOWTO.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">publish</a> the <a class="tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves" href="#PublicKey">PublicKey</a>.</p><pre><code>gpg ‐‐gen-key
gpg --edit-key me
&gt; addkey # RSA (sign only), 4096, 0
&gt; save</code></pre><p>Once that's done it should be simple to generate a <a class="tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves" href="#DetachedSignature">DetachedSignature</a> each time the website is published, which anyone can use to <a class="tc-tiddlylink-external" href="https://www.gnupg.org/gph/en/manual/x135.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">verify</a> that the HTML file is authentic.</p><pre><code>gpg --armor --output index.sig.txt --detach-sig index.html
gpg --verify index.sig.txt index.html</code></pre></div></content></entry><entry><title>2017-10-17 Topics of Interest</title><link href="http://jeffcaulfield.com/#2017-10-17%20Topics%20of%20Interest"></link><link href="http://jeffcaulfield.com/static/2017-10-17%2520Topics%2520of%2520Interest.html" rel="alternative" type="text/html"></link><id>8ad0660f-dc92-8f62-0ef6-169aab561be5</id><updated>2017-10-17T21:42:48</updated><content type="xhtml"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p>Here are a few topics that interest me. Perhaps I should write something about one or two of them.</p><ul><li><a class="tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves" href="#BlackdownHills">BlackdownHills</a></li><li><a class="tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves" href="#CellularAutomata">CellularAutomata</a></li><li><a class="tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves" href="#ChildrenOfADeadEarth">ChildrenOfADeadEarth</a></li><li><a class="tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves" href="#MicroscopeRPG">MicroscopeRPG</a></li><li><a class="tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves" href="#VimEditor">VimEditor</a></li></ul></div></content></entry><entry><title>2017-10-15 A Fresh Start</title><link href="http://jeffcaulfield.com/#2017-10-15%20A%20Fresh%20Start"></link><link href="http://jeffcaulfield.com/static/2017-10-15%2520A%2520Fresh%2520Start.html" rel="alternative" type="text/html"></link><id>00be44fa-eb77-8504-e4ce-8829c9801dce</id><updated>2017-10-15T22:14:31</updated><content type="xhtml"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p>I've always had a soft spot for <a class="tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves" href="#TiddlyWiki">TiddlyWiki</a> so I thought why not use it to rebuild my personal website.</p><p>I'm using <a class="tc-tiddlylink-external" href="http://tiddlywiki.com/#GettingStarted%20-%20Node.js" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Node.js</a> to work locally and then the <a class="tc-tiddlylink-external" href="http://tiddlywiki.com/#BuildCommand" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">BuildCommand</a> to generate the stand-alone HTML file.
</p></div></content></entry></feed>

